  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "The Chef has written all the numbers from **1** to **109** consecutively on a board. Let **P** be the long string \nobtained by concatenating the numbers written on the board consecutively. Given below are the first few digits of the long string **P**.\n\n\n\n`123456789101112131415161718192**02122**232425262728293031323334353637383940....`\n\n\n\nGiven another string **Q**, he is wondering whether **Q** is a substring of the string **P**. \nFor example, **Q**=\"02122\" is a substring of **P**, and has been marked in bold above.\n\n\n\n\n&nbsp;",
    "constraints": [
      "**1** ≤ **T** ≤ **10**",
      "**1** ≤ length of **Q** ≤ **100000 (105)**",
      "**Q** consists of only digits(0-9)",
      "&nbsp;",
      "Example**Input:**",
      "3",
      "23456789101",
      "3216546546546546545",
      "02122",
      "**Output:**",
      "YES",
      "NO",
      "YES"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "**T****T****Q**&nbsp;",
    "outputFormat": "**YES****P****NO**",
